fields.name: Brazil
fields.description: This coffee comes from the Cerrado region in Brazil and was produced by Jorge Bakarat. Jorge was a city boy by birth and a civil engineer by trade, but as a young man found himself in the coffee industry, and immediately, he knew that he had found his calling. This particular coffee has been processed using anaerobic fermentation - this process adds boozy qualities to the cup that remind us of rum while accentuating the strawberry flavours and giving the coffee an incredible fruit-forward profile. It also has a candy-like sweetness that can only be compared to bubblegum. d improve quality.

fields.name: Bolivia
fields.description: We're really pleased to have this coffee from Juana Gonzales' own farm, where Juana utilises new techniques and methods. As with last year, this coffee is honey-processed, meaning some of the fruit is left on the seed as it dries. As a result you have a super sweet coffee that can suit any brew method!

fields.name: Colombia
fields.description: We are incredibly excited to introduce our first certified organic coffee! El Rubi was produced by a group of farmers in the Tolima region of Colombia, each of the farmers holds a plot of land too small to produce an offering on its own, but the farmers in the region have banded together, each one receiving organic certification, and agreeing to produce high quality coffee for the specialty market. We love stories of collaboration like this one and are excited to support these farmers.

fields.name: El Salvador
fields.description: This coffee boasts hoards of complexity. It has a sticky, sweet orange marmalade acidity, with a big caramel sweetness that reminds us of butterscotch. While tasting this on the cupping table we were perplexed by one of the tasting notes, there was definitely chocolate in there, but it was slightly different to usual, and then we picked up that hint of coconut (an exciting, but unusual flavour to find in coffee) which rounds out the chocolate into a bounty bar like finish. This coffee has so much to offer, brew it in any brew method and you'll no doubt be delighted.

fields.name: Ethiopia
fields.description: Ana Sora is a fairly rare example of a private estate in Ethiopia, owned by Israel Degfa. It is a relatively new and large farm, sitting at extremely high altitudes near the town of Yirgacheffe. At the moment, all of the coffee on the farm is naturally processed, which gives this coffee a syrupy quality, with many of the exciting flavours common to coffees from this region.

fields.name: Ethiopia decaf
fields.description: Just because it's decaf doesn't mean it can't taste just as great as regular coffee! Our decaf is sourced and roasted with the same attention to detail as all our coffees and equally as delicious!

fields.name: Guatemala
fields.description: Guatemala in general is an exceptional coffee region with lots of great quality to offer! Watch this space because we are sure to have more where this coffee comes from. It is also our first time roasting a Villa Sarchi variety. This variety is a natural mutation of the Bourbon variety that originally occurred in Costa Rica, but because of its suitability to the climate, it has become quite popular throughout Central America. The Villa Sarchi variety offers excellent cup quality with nuanced acidity, great clarity, and prominent sweetness.

fields.name: Honduras
fields.description: Saul Moises has become a very influential coffee producers in central America. His name, or the name of his farm, La Cascada, can be seen in specialty coffee shops around the world and has become synonymous with excellent quality, experimental processing, and all-round great coffee. Needless to say, despite being our second coffee from him, we are no less excited about it!

fields.name: Nicaragua
fields.description: Las Nubes comes from several farms in The Cordillera Isabelia, a mountainous rainforest in Nicaragua. The area was one of the first to adapt to coffee production in Nicaragua, and traditional methods are still used. Las Nubes is an extremely complex coffee, refreshing and clean, an ideal summer coffee.

fields.name: Rwanda
fields.description: Our first Rwandan coffee in quite some time comes from Sholi, a co-op started by 30 women in the Cyeza region. Over the years Sholi has grown to include 610 local producers and has been the catalyst for revitalising the local community while producing excellent coffee. This washed bourbon is crisp and sweet, perfect for summer.

fields.name: Sweatshot 3fe
fields.description: Keep it cosy with our 3fe Crewneck

fields.name: Ocean bottle
fields.description: The original award-winning Ocean Bottle keeps cold drinks cold, and hot drinks hot. Made from double wall vacuum-insulated stainless steel and recycled content. The anti-leak dual opening lid makes filling and cleaning a breeze. Plus, unlike most reusable bottles, Ocean Bottle is 100% dishwasher safe.

fields.name: Scarf 3fe
fields.description: Show your support for your favourite local coffee roaster.

fields.name: Beanie Soma
fields.description: Represent your favourite local cafe (hint: it's us) this winter with Soma's new range of merch and swag. All of our merchandise supports local producers and the branding is from the work of local artists.

fields.name: Mug
fields.description: Tapio is a small Irish company who produce 8oz double-walled aluminium travel mugs. These mugs are stylishly designed and, with their incredible insulation, they can keep your coffee hot (or cold) for up to three hours. The cups are made from food-grade stainless steel. This means that they impart no odours or flavours to your drink; all that you will taste is your delicious tea or coffee!

fields.name: Aeropress
fields.description: The AeroPress is, without doubt, one of the most accomplished and recognized coffee brewers on the market today. It is a perfect coffee maker, no matter your skill level - from the experienced and avid coffee enthusiast to the casual mid-day office brewer, the AeroPress will always deliver. This begs the question: how do you improve on what is already an almost perfect coffee maker that is portable, virtually unbreakable, and one of the most versatile coffee makers in the world. Quite simple really, you just lean into these achievements by making it more portable and more robust!

fields.name: French Press
fields.description: Despite the French press falling to the sidelines with many specialty coffee aficionados, the French press has been an iconic favourite in the world of coffee brewing for many decades. You might even be surprised to hear that it remains the preferred brew method of most coffee roasters because French press brews are the closest to what you might find in a cupping bowl. The French press is a classic and versatile full immersion brewer that every kitchen needs.

fields.name: Moka Express
fields.description: There is nothing quite like real espresso. Its rich, decadent and syrupy body and flavour are second to none. Making real, authentic espresso requires a lot of high-end and expensive equipment, but a few very simply home brewers have managed to get extraordinarily close, and the original home espresso maker is the Bialetti Moka Express. While it is not quite espresso, it is one of the closest things we have and, more importantly, it brews delicious, intense, and full-bodied coffee! If you are an espresso lover, the Moka Express is a must-have home brewer for you!

fields.name: Coffee scale
fields.description: The ideal scales for home brewing, the Hario comes with both a time and weight digital display. This also fits most standard portafilters for those of you making home espresso.

fields.name: Tea Pot
fields.description: These beautiful and durable tea pots have a built in infuser and are available in Red, White, Blue & Grey

fields.name: Hario mini drip
fields.description: The Kasuya Range of Hario products are all designed with a beautiful and stylish matte black finish. When brewing a pour over, making sure that all the coffee is saturated evenly can make a big difference in your extraction and flavour. This kettle has a precision pouring spout and an ergonomic handle making each pour slow, directional, and precisely where you want it. By giving you extra control and precision, you can decide how fast the water flows and tweak your brews to perfection.

fields.name: Sage Barista Pro
fields.description: The Sage Barista Pro Espresso Machines allows you to make coffee shop quality espresso in one machine at home. The integrated conical burr grinder gives you full control of you grind size and dose of your coffee, while the ThermoJet heating system brings your machine up to temperature in 3 seconds. This allows you to brew a perfect espresso at home in no time. The powerful Sage steam wand produces latte-art worthy micro foam milk, so you will be pouring cappuccinos like a pro.

fields.name: Victoria Arduino grinder
fields.description: With the Mythos One, Victoria Arduino developed Clima Pro technology, which moved the boundaries of on demand coffee grinder operating temperatures; now with the new Clima Pro 2.0 system of Mythos 2, baristas can work with lower temperatures, thus expanding their range of choice. In addition to keep consistent the temperature in grinding chamber, Mythos 2 is also able to reduce it, to allow a more efficient work.

fields.name: Wilfa Coffee Grinder
fields.description: There are many manual grinders on the market today, some of them very reasonably priced and of excellent quality, however, the expectation that you need to manually grind your coffee before you've had your coffee is unreasonable at best. This is where the Wilfa Classic Electric Coffee Grinder comes into play and you begin your exploration of freshly ground coffee.
